    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Leviticus",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 19,
        "summary": "Israel is commanded: Be holy, live righteously, love your neighbor, and keep the commandments\u2014The Lord reveals and reaffirms sundry laws and commandments\u2014Enchantments, wizardry, prostitution, and all evil practices are forbidden.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Speak unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, and say unto them, Ye shall be holy: for I the Lord your God am holy.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0saints or holy ones. Josh. 24:19; Isa. 5:16; D&C 82:14. TG\u00a0God, the Standard of Righteousness; Holiness.",
                        "start": 90,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 122
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall fear every man his mother, and his father, and keep my sabbaths: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 59:9.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Turn ye not unto idols, nor make to yourselves molten gods: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Judg. 17:3 (3\u20134); 2\u00a0Ne. 9:37; D&C 1:16.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And if ye offer a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the Lord, ye shall offer it at your own will.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 76
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Moro. 7:6.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "It shall be eaten the same day ye offer it, and on the morrow: and if ought remain until the third day, it shall be burnt in the fire.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if it be eaten at all on the third day, it is abominable; it shall not be accepted.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 7:18; Ezek. 4:14.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 49
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore every one that eateth it shall bear his iniquity, because he hath profaned the hallowed thing of the Lord: and that soul shall be cut off from among his people.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 5:1 (1\u20136).",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not wholly reap the corners of thy field, neither shalt thou gather the gleanings of thy harvest.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Harvest.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ruth 2:2 (2, 12).",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 69
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ruth 2:8 (2\u20139); Mosiah 4:26; D&C 42:31.",
                        "start": 126,
                        "end": 135
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And thou shalt not glean thy vineyard, neither shalt thou gather every grape of thy vineyard; thou shalt leave them for the poor and stranger: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity; Poor; Welfare.",
                        "start": 124,
                        "end": 128
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall not steal, neither deal falsely, neither lie one to another.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stealing.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 136:25.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Lying.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And ye shall not swear by my name falsely, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Swearing.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Honesty.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Profanity.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 69
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not defraud thy neighbour, neither rob him: the wages of him that is hired shall not abide with thee all night until the morning.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 24:15. TG\u00a0Fraud.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Neighbor.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Wages.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not curse the deaf, nor put a stumblingblock before the blind, but shalt fear thy God: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Curse.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Compassion.",
                        "start": 25,
                        "end": 29
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 14:13.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 27:18.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 100,
                        "end": 102
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment: thou shalt not respect the person of the poor, nor honour the person of the mighty: but in righteousness shalt thou judge thy neighbour.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0injustice. Ex. 23:3 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 34,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0show unjust favoritism either to the humble or the mighty. Deut. 1:17; D&C 38:25 (25\u201327).",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 148
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not go up and down as a talebearer among thy people: neither shalt thou stand against the blood of thy neighbour: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip; Honesty.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 45
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not hate thy brother in thine heart: thou shalt in any wise rebuke thy neighbour, and not suffer sin upon him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Though you may reprove a neighbor and not tolerate his sin, do not hate him. Jacob 2:7; D&C 121:43.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hardheartedness.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not avenge, nor bear any grudge against the children of thy people, but thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forbear; Retribution.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Malice.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Charity; Love.",
                        "start": 94,
                        "end": 98
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fellowshipping; Neighbor.",
                        "start": 103,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 127,
                        "end": 129
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall keep my statutes. Thou shalt not let thy cattle gender with a diverse kind: thou shalt not sow thy field with mingled seed: neither shall a garment mingled of linen and woollen come upon thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Note that these laws are in harmony with the other admonitions to keep things pure and in proper use. TG\u00a0Separation.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 31
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 22:9.",
                        "start": 119,
                        "end": 126
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 22:11.",
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 164
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And whosoever lieth carnally with a woman, that is a bondmaid, betrothed to an husband, and not at all redeemed, nor freedom given her; she shall be scourged; they shall not be put to death, because she was not free.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0a man.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0there shall be an investigation or inquisition.",
                        "start": 136,
                        "end": 157
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 175
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 48,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall bring his trespass offering unto the Lord, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, even a ram for a trespass offering.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the priest shall make an atonement for him with the ram of the trespass offering before the Lord for his sin which he hath done: and the sin which he hath done shall be forgiven him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Forgive.",
                        "start": 173,
                        "end": 181
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And when ye shall come into the land, and shall have planted all manner of trees for food, then ye shall count the fruit thereof as uncircumcised: three years shall it be as uncircumcised unto you: it shall not be eaten of.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But in the fourth year all the fruit thereof shall be holy to praise the Lord withal.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 85
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And in the fifth year shall ye eat of the fruit thereof, that it may yield unto you the increase thereof: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 108,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall not eat any thing with the blood: neither shall ye use enchantment, nor observe times.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Blood, Eating of.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0you shall not divine or use sorcery.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 50
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Kgs. 21:6; 2\u00a0Ne. 10:15; 26:22 (22\u201323).",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 18:14; Isa. 47:13 (13\u201315).",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 26
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall not round the corners of your heads, neither shalt thou mar the corners of thy beard.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0by cutting the forelocks of the hair of the head. Lev. 21:5.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall not make any cuttings in your flesh for the dead, nor print any marks upon you: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 18:28. TG\u00a0Mourning.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Body, Sanctity of.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 93
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Do not prostitute thy daughter, to cause her to be a whore; lest the land fall to whoredom, and the land become full of wickedness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 23:17 (17\u201318).",
                        "start": 7,
                        "end": 17
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Whore.",
                        "start": 82,
                        "end": 90
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0lewdness.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall keep my sabbaths, and reverence my sanctuary: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 23:3.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 25
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reverence.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Regard not them that have familiar spirits, neither seek after wizards, to be defiled by them: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0Do not turn to magic or necromancy.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Spirits, Evil or Unclean.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorcery.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Superstitions.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 99
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt rise up before the hoary head, and honour the face of the old man, and fear thy God: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0rise before the face of old age.",
                        "start": 11,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 20:29.",
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 35
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Courtesy; Family, Children, Duties of; Respect.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 98,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And if a stranger sojourn with thee in your land, ye shall not vex him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0oppress.",
                        "start": 63,
                        "end": 66
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But the stranger that dwelleth with you shall be unto you as one born among you, and thou shalt love him as thyself; for ye were strangers in the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Fellowshipping; Stranger.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0as a citizen of yours.",
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 10:19. TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 163,
                        "end": 165
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment, in meteyard, in weight, or in measure.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0injustice.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 30
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Just balances, just weights, a just ephah, and a just hin, shall ye have: I am the Lord your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 25:13.",
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 27
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 25:15 (14\u201315); Ezek. 45:10; Amos 8:5.",
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 78
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore shall ye observe all my statutes, and all my judgments, and do them: I am the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}